sermons.title: The Transcendence of El Elyon
sermons.description: The principal names of GOD, found in Psalm 91:1-2, gather up the unique glory that belongs to Him. They deserve attention as they show us what God is in His inmost nature. In this message focus is on “the Most High God”, EL Elyon, meaning one who is “elevated, or lofty.” He is Supreme One, MOST HIGH above all created beings in heaven and earth – a Divine transcendence that sees Him exalted so far above the universe He created that human thought cannot even imagine it. You can trust El Elyon to unfailingly furnish you with all you will ever need in order to fulfil His will.
